caption: I tried to have lunch with a friend here today. From the get go, the host was militant, angry and unwelcoming to the point that we felt so uncomfortable that we had to leave.
Good sushi with very COVID friendly staff and experience.
Loved it!
They have the freshest food and some of the best sushi on the northside and the service is always friendly and consistent
Sushi here is amongst the best in the city and their soups are delicious

Great find! I've passed this restaurant several times during walks and had no idea what a sushi gem it is! I ordered delivery and was very impressed with how well everything was packaged. All of the rolls and cooked appetizers were fresh, delicious, and filling! I loved that the flavors of the ingredients are the stars, instead of overwhelming spice and salt. My bf and I especially appreciate Indie after trying several different places in the area that are too salty, too heavy, and too expensive for what they offer. Thank you, Indie! I strongly recommend you contact the restaurant directly for delivery because the service was stellar and the order took half the time it would usually take with GH.The delivery gentleman was very polite and arrived within an hour of my order placed. Can't wait to order again!
It was pretty good! The Tom ka kai soup has a really interesting flavor and tasted good on a cold night. The basil chicken entree was plenty to share and we had a nice night out!
First time going to this little sushi joint and I absolutely loved it. Very reasonable prices especially for sushi.

I have ordered from Indie Cafe at lease three or four times. The sushi is always fantastic. It is fun to try the different varieties. I've been ordering on the phone and picking up because of the Pandemic, so I don't have experience dining in. However, my experience with pick-up has been easy and fast; employees are friendly.
Food is delicious!! Service is great.

This is The Best Thai & Japanese Restaurant I visit when I'm in the Edgewater Neighborhood. Everything is so Fresh!! Really nothing but enjoyable experience here. Yesterday, Monday about 1pm I was craving Sushi and I was in the area so I called to place the order. Hubs ordered the Indie Duo Don (Salmon & Tuna) His favorite! I had the V- Temp (Sweet Potato & Asparagus) I don't know what they do but it taste so crunchy and light. Also ordered the Fire Komodo Maki (soft Shell crab, cream cheese, cucumber topped with broiled eel) Everything just taste so good together. Last and not least I also had the Santa Fe Maki (shrimp Tempura, cucumber, lettuce,  spicy mayo & Avocado) Perfect for a 1 bite! Seriously, Recommend to try this place if your in the Edgewater area.
It was a great experience guys, thanks!

Indie is a great local spot. They have all of the Thai favorites and I would say that the sushi is a strong point as well as general atmosphere. The lunch special is a good deal, though in my experience there can be inconsistencies between visits from time to time which is what stops me from being all-in about this place.
Great food and packaged very carefully! 10/10
Always worth visiting. Creative presentation, wonderfully fresh. Highly recommend Indie.

The sushi was fresh, the service polite, the tab reasonable. My friend and I dined outside on a sunny autumn afternoon: it was a perfect luncheon. A plus: the samosa starter was delicious. A diappointment: the tea served from a tea bag

Food is good but the portions have gotten smaller. I just ordered as a matter fact today and I ordered a red curry Pad Thai with tofu and I received the same size cup as my miso soup and Tom Yum soup?! Ms. Pear stated, "Last time you asked for extra sauce and extra eggplant but you didn't say anything this time." Hahaha !! 🙄

This spot is one of my favorites! Fair prices, large portions and excellent sushi. Great quality ingredients prepared. Absolutely one of the best Omakase. Great food, great atmosphere and best sake selection.
Always a go-to, as someone who lives in the heart of downtown, I willingly come here multiple times a month for some of the best food this city has to offer. Highly recommended.

The sushi is so fresh and delicious! Some of the best I have ever had. The service...not so much. Been twice in a week for patio dining. Paid at time of order and gave a 20% tip. Ordered about 75 in sushi and a bottle of wine. The server never checked on us and we would have bought a second bottle. Second visit I left the tab open, ordered about the same amount and had to ask for them to wipe the table outside. The server came out and barely brushed it off with a paper towel. Again, they never came out to check on us. When we closed out I could only justify a 10% tip. It pains me not to tip at least 20% when I dine out. Oh and guess what? We were the only customers. The reason for four stars is the service. Would love to give them 5. With that said we will be back, but we will bring wet wipes and ask them to check on us.
Great food! Great service! Clean and neat.
Great, friendly service and always excellent sushi even during the pandemic!
The food is regularly well prepared and delicious, cashiers hands out great service. I loved how neat it is and mood. I highly recommend this place.
excellent place to dine..

This is a great restaurant with great food, service, and ambiance. They reserve a specific table if you want a particular table in the restaurant and they provide an ice bucket if you bring a chilled wine or champagne. Great place!

I really enjoyed dinner here with friends on a Friday night. We were seated right away and they were able to provide a table big enough to accommodate a baby in a car seat. We had only sushi and the Almond Monkey maki roll was my favorite - so good we ordered another one!
Indie is always perfection. Easily the best restaurant in Roger's park, and handily the best sushi in Chicago. The salmon almond maki is legendary, my mouth is watering at the thought!

Not only is the presentation beautiful each and every time but the food is consistantly delicious. I've been bringing friends and out of town guests to this little gem of a restaurant in Edgewater since it opened in 2004. Menu is so robust that you might have a difficult time choosing but everything is so good that you can't go wrong.
Food is delicious, especially the kampyo maki. There's plenty of options for vegetarians.

Let me start this post off by saying that I do not like sushi, it is not my first choice but I am open to trying new food therefore we came here to eat and I had sushi. And I liked it, it was pretty yummy! They bring it out very nicely plated which is a plus as it is pleasing to the eyes and also tastes delish! We also got the crab rangoons which were also delicious! And the fried rice that was also delicious. Nothing bad to say here, definitely a must try if you don’t fancy sushi!

Friendly staff. Great atmosphere in the afternoon. Food was absolutely spot on. Asked for my pad ke mao  (drunken noodle) to be Thai hot, they delivered a dish that had great flavor, and got progressively hotter over time, but just in case they brought me more spices in case I wanted it hotter still.  The Thai Iced Tea was delicious.  Sushi was suuuuuper fresh for being in the middle of the US. The only thing I can really "critique" is that the wasabi was actually pretty tame. To be fair, it may have been the day. If I return to Chicago, I'm returning here for sure.

We live in the neighborhood in Edgewater and we frequent here a lot. The food is great and prices are good. Service it's always prompt. It's all BYOB!! We should be back soon!

I had such a great experience at lunch the day before that I had to come back for dinner the next day. Amazing and authentic ramen and noodle bowls here and I love how much you can customize your orders to add heat or whatever hanking you may have for delicious pork belly or gyoza. Try the thai iced tea if you haven't, such a treat. I highly recommend this place, you will not be disappointed.

Great local restaurant. Extensive (and bewildering) pan-asian menu. Not sure if that's a good or a bad thing but everything tastes wonderful. Often get takeout from there too which is fast and the same quality as eating in. I know people come from miles around to go here.

Good decor, not so good food.  Had chive dumplings. Instead of pan frying, they deep fried the dumpling. So you ended up with a hard, tasteless item that tasted like the outside of an overcooked egg roll. I also had the philly maki. The salmon tasted room temperature and definitely not fresh. Green tea, generic. I asked for a mineral water, they gave me  a bottle of cheap regular water distilled by the coke company. Pathetic  where are the grown up restaurateurs?  The sushi staff did not even have their hair covered. Eww!
Love Thai. Love indie
Great Ramen! I love Tamago sushi too. It is huge and delicious! The waitresses are friendly. It's a clean place but when there are many customers, the place does become noisy.

Hands down the best sushi-cum-thai joint in Edgewater. Eat here.

I love this place!  I used to live in the neighborhood and shopped at Whole Foods up the street and found it hard to resist every time I went grocery shopping. The lunch special is such a great deal. I like that they offer Thai and sushi versions of the lunch special. The sushi is really good. I love the tempura sweet potato roll.  It's ridiculous. The thai food is good too. I really do not have anything  bad to say aside from I wish I still lived closer.

For the quality of the food, this place is deserving of five stars!  The trio carpaccio,  poke bowls,  sashimi, and skewers (the items I've eaten thus far) were delicious.  Having said that,  it was a pretty terrible impression by the waitress the first and only time I've actually eaten at the restaurant.   We walk in as the only customers there asking to sit on the patio and she asks,  "You want to sit outside now?"  We respond with a "yes" not grasping her skepticism.   She then says,  "It's too cold.  I'll sit you by the window."  It was a sunny day in the mid 50s and didn't expect her to sit out there with us.  As a former server,  it was a rude way of addressing the situation and her demeanor didn't get better.  In conclusion,  I think it's a fine establishment.  I'll just be sticking to delivery from here on.

Don't get me wrong,  first time we visit this place. We walked in. Were seated right away. We ordered the Chive fried dumplings wow amazig, fatty part of salmon (it has a name I don't remember) those two were appetizers and they care right away, we has an alcoholic drink and a ginger tea. We also order a curry and a maki roll. We sat there talking and drinking and eating. I saw my maki roll sitting by the sushi bar ok soon it will be here 7 minutes later I saw two people standing right by it doing stuff plus customers passing by to use the restroom at least 3 or 4. Then is almost 20 minutes waiting and we started to wonder why we do not have our food. The server comes over and tell us the maki roll is ready but the curry is not do you want your food. I said no, that food has been sitting there for a long time with a few of you breathing on my food, that is nasty.  She gave me a look like I asked to kiss my shoes. She said she can get me a new one. No idea if I got a new one or not i never saw them making a new one. The curry came almost 5 or 7 minutes later by now is 30 minutes waiting for our main dishes. Ok Sex on the moon maki roll was bad, omg tasteless, nothing good about it. However,  the curry was coconut milk red curry with fried chicken OMG  so good. That was the only thing it was worthy of our meal. Would I try again yes. But only take out, all the servers are so careless, almost rude. Nice place with funky wall art.

Always delicious, and reasonably priced. Good selection of sushi, rice and noodle dishes, and curries. They have a nice little patio out front perfect to sit oitside on nice evenings. One of my favorite restaurants in the area.

I feel like this place is a solid staple on Broadway.  I normally order thai items off the menu but I've had the sushi and miso soup as well.  I've never disliked anything I've had here and I've ordered takeout from them more times that I would like to admit.  Their basil chicken is perfect if you add eggplant!
Lovely place. Excellent food choices and very kind wait staff. Try the teriyaki!

Well I assumed, since this is the only sushi joint that serves alcohol in Edgewater, that it would have good food.  I was wrong, and shame on me for thinking such a stupid thing.  The sushi was uninspiring, the wonton was almost burnt to an inedible scolding mess in my mouth, and the service was consistently absent.  I felt like I wasn't even welcome there with the awkward wait and seating.  And there were several tables that were "reserved" next to the windows that never showed up.  The server never asked us how we were or seemed to care that we were there.  The place was barely 1/3 full even by 6:30pm when we left.  So how is there any excuse for such absent and flaky service?  As far as the food, I was warned when I ordered the Kimono roll, that it would be REALLY spicy.  Really?  Spicy?  Spicy Nacho Doritos have tasted spicier.  It was bland, unexciting and fell apart often.  You may try to put on a trendy facade, Indie Cafe, but you didn't follow through with any positive experience.  Making your food look fancy and serving alcohol with the option of BYOB just doesn't cut it.  For those with the need for a gimmicky place to eat, here you go.
I've only had Thai food here, it's really good and the service as well my only complain is that the layout of the place makes it feel too crowded even when there's not too many people.

This place is great!

Earned a rare five stars due to an excellent combination of flavor, presentation, service, ambiance, and value. The tuna roll was nearly perfect. The signature curry beef earned a rare rave review from my girlfriend. She said that the ingredients were fresh, the beef was melt in your mouth, and the sauce was rich, creamy, and delicious.

I love it here.  The food is delicious (SO many choices) as are the drinks.  The service is fast and efficient without being too pushy.  The only thing I don't like is that it gets crowded ... but, there's a reason for that! :-)

The service is always great here and it's usually pretty easy to get in on the weekends even without a reservation after 8pm.

One of my favorite restaurants on the north side.  The food, service and atmosphere are great and the prices are reasonable.  I've been a customer since restaurant opened and I've never been disappointed.

Chef Iggy Waranon and Co-Owner Gui Prasartkul came to Chicago in 1998 with intent to study art. With the help of their roommate and friend, they developed a menu with a fusion of Thai and Japanese cuisine inspired by their passion for art. The combination of Iggy’s cooking experience and Gui’s business acumen, the Indie Café emerged in 2004. Ever since, Indie has opened, it has become an original Chicago restaurant. The logo shows much of what Indie is about. The logo is an octopus which its legs represents the diverse influences and techniques brought to the cooking. The cuisine of Thai and Japanese is presented in an elegant artistic matter. They stretch boundaries to develop dishes without changing the roots of both cuisines. Its interior design is surely a sight to see, from the comfortable black lounge seats to the colorful paintings on the wall. It seems to me that they put just as much thought into the décor as the menu. The first time you step in you can see the sushi chef preparing food in the middle of the room. It is very colorful and has a nice window view of the street of Broadway. They hang paintings up on the wall that all share a similar style, but don’t look too long. The art is very different and can cause you to stare at it for a while. They have unique lightings, which looks like woven circular silk shades that illuminate the room. The dishes that the food comes out in are plain white square plates, in order to keep the consumer’s eye more focused on the art of the food. Many people walk in, mostly families or couples. Everyone that walks in is very friendly and has already come once before. Indie has many regular customers around the neighborhood. Indie Café lies between Western, Irving Park, June Wayne, and Lakeshore. The restaurant can be accessed by CTA. In between Thorndale and Grandville of the Red-line is found right around the corners. It is convenient for many Chicagoans to get to, and at any time you want. The restaurant is open from 11am to 10pm, except on Tuesday. The menu in Indie is absolutely huge. The menu is very unique and you will not find it anywhere else. From the appetizers to the desserts you will enjoy almost if not all the food listed on there. There is also a wine and beer menu just as large as their food menu.  The portions are not large but definitely worth the price. The dishes always come out with a wow factor. They arrange to plate in a way that you much rather stare at it than eat it. The food satisfies your taste as well as your sight. The dishes are made well, and are not rushed. I feel that with the way the food looks and taste they should raise their prices. Did I also mention they have a catering and delivery service? The waitresses are very friendly and always have a smile on their faces. The employees make sure that your experience there is the best and that you come back for more. In conclusion, if you want a nice restaurant to have a family dinner or a simple date that is wallet friendly, I one hundred percent recommend that anyone who enjoys Asian cuisine and/or art. The food is amazing for its somewhat cheap prices. The service they offer is absolutely the best. If you live around the neighborhood they could just deliver their awesome food to your door step or cater at your next party! How many fusion restaurants do you know that have a catering business? This is truly a one of a kind restaurant found in Chicago.

5 Stars for their atmosphere! The restaurant is decorated with fun whimsical art! It's a fun place to meet friends for dinner. They serve Thai and Japanese food...which means they don't do any of it really well but it is good. Just not my first choice for sushi or Thai.
